> Ruvector Review gemini · domain: `ruvector/retrieval`. Generated with [create-agent-gemini](https://github.com/ruvnet/agent-gemini-generator).

## Behavioral rules

- Use the gemini's MCP tools (`mcp__{{name}}__*`) for orchestration
- Memory and routing are handled by the kernel — you don't need to learn them
- Defer destructive operations to the user

## Agents

| Agent | Tier | Role |
|---|---|---|
| `indexer` | sonnet | Chunks and embeds the corpus. |
| `retriever` | sonnet | Runs HNSW search with citations. |
| `reviewer` | opus | Grades the answer against the sources. |
## Skills

- `/memory-inspect` — Search and inspect the gemini memory namespace (HNSW + emergent-time decay).
- `/index-and-ask` — Index a corpus into ruvector and answer a question with reviewed citations.

## Commands

- `doctor` — Health-check the gemini: kernel load, MCP wiring, memory backend, host adapter.

## Architecture

This gemini uses [@metaharness/kernel](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metaharness/kernel) — a Rust-compiled WASM module with a NAPI-RS native fallback — so the same code runs identically on every platform.
